JOHANNESBURG – Proteas fast bowler Lungi Ngidi is expected to head back to South Africa from the Indian Premier League (IPL) following his father's death on Friday. Jerome Ngidi passed away at a KwaZulu-Natal hospital, and is survived by his wife, Bongi, and four sons of which Ngidi is the youngest. READ: Former Bloemfontein Celtic owner Molemela dies Cricket South Africa (CSA) has sent condolences to Ngidi along with his family, following the sudden passing of his father. “Cricket South Africa is shocked and deeply saddened by the passing away of Mr Ngidi. We would like to extend our most sincere condolences to Lungi and his family. May the Lord be with him and comfort the rest of the Ngidi family during this difficult time,” said CSA president, Chris Nenzani. African News Agency